theorem not_mem_closure_iff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} {x : X} :
    x ∉ closure A ↔ ∃ U : Set X, IsOpen U ∧ x ∈ U ∧ U ∩ A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  classical
  constructor
  · intro hNot
    have h : ¬ ∀ U : Set X, IsOpen U → x ∈ U → (U ∩ A).Nonempty := by
      intro hAll
      have hx : x ∈ closure A := (mem_closure_iff).2 hAll
      exact hNot hx
    push_neg at h
    rcases h with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hEmpty⟩
    have hEq : U ∩ A = (∅ : Set X) :=
      (Set.not_nonempty_iff_eq_empty).1 hEmpty
    exact ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hEq⟩
  · rintro ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hEq⟩
    intro hxCl
    have hNon : (U ∩ A).Nonempty := (mem_closure_iff).1 hxCl U hU_open hxU
    have : False := by
      simpa [hEq] using hNon
    exact this
